al fun last night. I love dongion hunting but after 4 or 5 hours of it, it's nice to get out in the open and just screw around.  Had a elite Ry'Gorr following me around for like 30 minutes tring to kill it just to see if we could do it! lol <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umrgoodkin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mr Goodkin </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/3/02 3:38:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A bard and a ranger?</span><hr size=1> On old blue server, when my brother in law and I were early 50's, we could take down a mob faster than a full group of mid 40's.  He is a bard and I a rogue.  <br><br>I know what you mean about fun parnters.  I also partnered with a monk in FM at fort and that was a hoot taking a mob that usually a whole group near us was having problems at the same level and we were both 29.  But it did hurt.<br><br>As a blackguard, I grouped with SK's and Necros in the grey.  Lethal combos.  The rogue epic is phenomenal.<br><br>Thank you again for helping me out with getting my banded pieces I needed.  I truly appreciated your effort that night.<br><br>/wave <p>May Brell shine the light in your eyes ~ <BR> Goody <BR> Firiona Vie</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ublakkon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>blakkon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 275<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/3/02 11:35:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Shaman and Monk</span><hr size=1> Though I reap the benefits, I often feel this combo should be nerfed <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br> <p>Lorec <br>Wandering Judge of the Tribunal <br>Excellent Tailor <br>Master Baker <br>Lousy Smith <br>Master Brewer <br>Master  Drunk <br>Aspiring Polyglot <br>Wannabe Alchemist <br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uuininstormsong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Uinin Stormsong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/3/02 11:46:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Meat Grinder</span><hr size=1> As a bard, I can honestly say that the Ranger-Bard duo is an evil sucker punch.  The &quot;Hybrid Heaven&quot; tandem is one of the best I've come across, with both classes complementing the other.  Plus - luckily for me - most rangers have delusions of warriorhood and like to distract the business end of the MOB so I can safely poke it with a stick.<br><br>However, I've found nothing quite like the three-bard buzzsaw.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :o --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/embarassed.gif ALT=":o"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  That was fun! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ugorgash.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gorgash<